Sorry, should have thought it a little further through before posting, but a coupe of additional notes on said spinal fracture:

-The trick, if you're thinking about incorporating this injury is to either make it humorous or add it as a slice of life. As an example, you could have your main character rail some excitable waifur with authority, then have her accidentally set his back off by tackling him / pulling him into a hug funny while lying down. You can have him talk a big game to a dom of a character, only to have him sputtering about how he can't be strapped into a torsion rig because he wants to be able to walk tomorrow.
-Stable fractures like that CAN be fused, but the doctors would have to fuse the full vertebrae to the one above it (and possibly below it) which brings its own problems / potential complications.
-Off axis oblique twists, and vertical compression are what usually set it off. Controlled motions are usually alright, because the spinal erectors can keep things (more or less) stable.
